# Styling Patterns

This project uses **Tailwind CSS 4** with **shadcn/ui** components. shadcn/ui uses Radix UI primitives under the hood, but we follow shadcn/ui conventions and patterns.

## Tailwind CSS

### Configuration

- **Version**: Tailwind CSS 4.1.18
- **Config**: PostCSS-based configuration
- **Theme**: Custom theme with CSS variables

### Utility Classes

Use Tailwind utility classes for styling:

```typescript
<div className="flex flex-col gap-y-2 p-4 rounded-lg bg-card">
  <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">Title</h2>
</div>
```

### Class Name Merging

Use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  'base-classes',
  condition && 'conditional-classes',
  className // Allow prop override
)} />
```

## UI Components

### Component Location

Base UI components are in `src/components/ui/`:
- `button.tsx`
- `input.tsx`
- `card.tsx`
- `select.tsx`
- `dialog.tsx`
- etc.

### Using UI Components

```typescript
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card';

<Card>
  <Input placeholder="Enter text" />
  <Button variant="default">Submit</Button>
</Card>
```

### Component Variants

Components use `class-variance-authority` (CVA) for variants:

```typescript
// Example button variants
<Button variant="default">Default</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">Ghost</Button>
<Button size="sm">Small</Button>
<Button size="lg">Large</Button>
```

## shadcn/ui Components

The project uses **shadcn/ui** components, which are built on top of Radix UI primitives. We follow shadcn/ui conventions:

- Components are in `src/components/ui/`
- Use shadcn/ui component APIs and patterns
- Components are customizable and follow shadcn/ui design principles
- Underlying Radix UI primitives are abstracted away

## Theme System

### Theme Provider

Theme is managed via `next-themes`:

```typescript
import ThemeProvider from '@/components/theme/ThemeProvider';

// In root layout
<ThemeProvider>
  {children}
</ThemeProvider>
```

### Theme Switcher

```typescript
import ThemeSwitcher from '@/components/theme/ThemeSwitcher';

<ThemeSwitcher />
```

### CSS Variables

Theme uses CSS variables for colors:

```css
:root {
  --background: 0 0% 100%;
  --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  /* ... */
}
```

## Layout Patterns

### Flexbox Layouts

```typescript
// Column layout
<div className="flex flex-col gap-y-4">

// Row layout
<div className="flex flex-row gap-x-4 items-center">

// Responsive
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
```

### Grid Layouts

```typescript
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
```

### Spacing

Use consistent spacing scale:
- `gap-2` (0.5rem)
- `gap-4` (1rem)
- `p-4` (padding)
- `m-4` (margin)

## Form Styling

Form field components handle styling internally using the `Field`, `FieldLabel`, and `FieldError` components from `@/components/ui/field`. Use form field components from `@/components/form/fields/`:

```typescript
import { InputText } from '@/components/form/fields/InputText';

// Form field with label
<InputText name="title" label="Title" placeholder="Enter title" />

// Form field without label (label handled elsewhere)
<InputText name="email" placeholder="Email" />
```

The form field components automatically handle:
- Label display (if provided)
- Input styling
- Error message display
- React Hook Form integration

See `forms.mdc` for more details on form field patterns.

## Responsive Design

Use Tailwind breakpoints:

```typescript
// Mobile first
<div className="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">
<div className="hidden md:block">Desktop only</div>
<div className="block md:hidden">Mobile only</div>
```

## Icons

Use **Lucide React** for icons. **Always use the "Icon" suffix convention** when importing icons:

```typescript
import { PlusIcon, TrashIcon, EditIcon } from 'lucide-react';

<Button>
  <PlusIcon className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
  Add
</Button>
```

**Naming Convention**: Always import icons with the "Icon" suffix (e.g., `PlusIcon`, `TrashIcon`, `EditIcon`, `ArrowLeftRightIcon`, `UserCogIcon`, `LoaderCircleIcon`). This convention makes it clear that these are icon components.

## Animation

Use `tw-animate-css` for animations:

```typescript
<div className="animate-fade-in">
```

## Best Practices

1. **Use utility classes** - Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
2. **Consistent spacing** - Use Tailwind spacing scale
3. **Responsive design** - Mobile-first approach
4. **Component composition** - Build complex UIs from base components
5. **Theme-aware** - Use CSS variables for theme support
6. **Accessibility** - shadcn/ui components (built on Radix UI) are accessible by default
7. **Dark mode** - Theme system supports dark mode automatically

## Custom Styles

Global styles are in `src/app/globals.css`:

```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

@layer base {
  /* Base styles */
}
```
